{
  "stem": "20142.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we could tell that they were not Germans from Germany but-- and not-- they are not soldiers.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were the local people who want to take advantage of-- of the Jewish population.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that's how it was.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They came-- they're brutalizing people.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were beating them up for any reason whatsoever.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, on several occasion.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Can I tell-- yes, they came to-- if they have seen that a man and-- elderly man it was standing and he was without any support of-- of the other people, they were brutalizing him and beating him up and taking his cane away and beating him with a cane until the poor man fell down and they had to be taken away to-- to-- ambulance or-- or be taken away by other people and clear out-- out of the way.",
      "word_count": 81
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there were people begging them to stop beating them and kicking them and brutalizing them.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The local German people with these arm bands.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I remember at least three such incidents and-- in different part of Lodz.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And these people, of course, were privileged.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They had in their lapel, their little hakenkruis with the red circle.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you could tell that they were people who were living in Poland and knew every movement and trick that anybody else could do-- have.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And of course, they were working as the German informers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They spoke fluently Polish and understood quite a bit of Yiddish too, because of the similarity of the-- phonetic similarity.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I was speaking mostly Polish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Yiddish I learned during the times of camps.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not to extent that I could communicate.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I could communicate in Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "All right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, sure.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Standing-- there were-- there were curfew hours from 5 o'clock in the morning till 5 o'clock in the afternoon.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
